Main questions and challenges of methodology in social sciences. How to find a good method for your research problem? Quantitative and qualitative approaches, experiment, big data, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give thorough knowledge of the general methodology of social sciences and provide basic knowledge about data gathering and analyses for measuring and understanding the various processes in society and organizations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student: 
* knows the main terms and conceptions of the methodology of social sciences;
* is able to formulate a research problem and find a methodological solution;
* knows the main data gathering and analysis techniques and is able to use;
* is able to reflect critically upon his/her methodological experiences;
* is able to design and conduct a survey.
